        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Preconditions:</p>

<p><b>System Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Fast Delivery API service is running and accessible</li>
	<li>Base URL is configured and reachable</li>
	<li>API endpoint <tt>/fast-delivery/v3.1.1/calculate-delivery.xml</tt> is available</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Test Environment Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Postman is installed and configured</li>
	<li>Valid base URL is available for testing</li>
	<li>Network connectivity to the API service</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Data Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>productsCount = 3 (valid product count)</li>
	<li>productsWeight = 5 (valid weight value)</li>
	<li>deliveryTime = 0 (outside operating hours for boundary testing)</li>
</ul>


<p>Steps for reproducer:</p>

<p>1.Open Postman<br/>
2.Set request type to POST<br/>
3.Enter URL: <span class="error">&#91;base_url&#93;</span>/fast-delivery/v3.1.1/calculate-delivery.xml<br/>
4.Remove any path parameters (Fast Delivery API doesn't use kit IDs)<br/>
5.Set request body with productsCount=3, productsWeight=5, deliveryTime=0<br/>
6.Send request to Fast Delivery service<br/>
7.Verify Fast Delivery service is unavailable outside operating hours (isItPossibleToDeliver=false)<br/>
8.User gets Status: 200 OK with unavailable delivery response</p>

<p>Expected results:</p>

<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Status: 200 OK</li>
</ul>


<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>isItPossibleToDeliver = false</li>
</ul>


<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Message: Fast Delivery service unavailable outside operating hours</li>
</ul>


<p>Actual results:</p>

<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Status: 200 OK &lt;response name="Fast Delivery"/&gt;</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
